\frac {n\left[(n+1)\dots(n+r)\right]}{(r+1)!}+\frac {\left[(n+1)\dots(n+r)\right]}{r!}=\frac {\left[(n+1)\dots(n+r)\right](n+r+1)}{(r+1)!}
\sum_{k=1}^n\binom {k+r-1}r=\binom {n+r}{r+1}
r=1
